<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><?ish ishref="GUID-1F6EC30D-1C65-4922-A272-F5FEE55E2ABF" version="1" lang="en-US"?><task xmlns:ditaarch="http://dita.oasis-open.org/architecture/2005/" id="GUID-1F6EC30D-1C65-4922-A272-F5FEE55E2ABF" xml:lang="en-US" ditaarch:DITAArchVersion="1.3" domains="(topic task)                            (topic hi-d)                            (topic ui-d)                            (topic sw-d)                            (topic indexing-d)                            (topic ut-d)                            a(base ishcondition)                            a(base varid)                            a(base varref)                            a(base cid)                            a(base partslist)                            (topic oce-d)                            (topic sdlVariables-c)                            (topic oceCommonElements-c)                            (topic oceMetaDecl-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c task oceTask-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c hi-d oceHighlight-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c ui-d oceUi-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c sw-d oceSoftware-c)   " class="- topic/topic task/task "><title class="- topic/title ">Heavy transport of the printer</title><abstract class="- topic/abstract " id="M028334-B18"><p class="- topic/p ">This document describes the heavy transport of a printer.
</p><p class="- topic/p ">A heavy transport means: 
</p><ul class="- topic/ul "><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">After the 1<sup class="+ topic/ph hi-d/sup ">st</sup> installation the printer needs to be re-located to another building. The transport is over an uneven floor or bumpy street. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">The printer needs to be packed completely including transport brackets, foam but without sheet, bag and crate. 
</p></li></ul></abstract><prolog class="- topic/prolog "><metadata class="- topic/metadata "><category class="- topic/category ">Installation</category></metadata></prolog><taskbody class="- topic/body task/taskbody "><section id="SECTION_3EAAE870561847F1914DAA1BC10E2FD6" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Required tools</title><ul id="UL_3397BAAC9D5940BDBB97249F1BE4C31D" class="- topic/ul "><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> 2 People are required to carry out this procedure. 
</p></li></ul></section><section id="SECTION_BB8C533001C043A9B5E24F6EEECB8B53" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Personal protection</title><note type="caution" id="GUID-C8810ABE-05AA-47B2-A506-D909EB952778" class="- topic/note "><p class="- topic/p ">Wear safety shoes when working with heavy material (e.g. installation) or dis-assemblies of units. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">Wear protected clothing for protection of your personal clothing. 
</p></note></section><section id="GUID-94C20406-75A1-4BD0-A7DB-8CD9777F04B0" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Procedure</title><table id="NEW" class="- topic/table "><tgroup align="left" outputclass="step" cols="3" class="- topic/tgroup "><colspec colname="col1" colnum="1" colwidth="10*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col2" colnum="2" colwidth="50*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col3" colnum="3" colwidth="40*" class="- topic/colspec "/><thead valign="top" class="- topic/thead "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Step 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Action 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Remarks 
</p></entry></row></thead><tbody valign="top" class="- topic/tbody "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">1 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Do 
<xref keyref="INSTGEN099" class="- topic/xref " href="GUID-1DD95CE3-6D43-4D11-A25D-09973878659B.xml" format="dita" locktitle="yes" type="task"><?ditaot usertext?><?xm-replace_text Packing instruction of a used printer (todo)?>Packing instruction of a used printer</xref> 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "/></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">2 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><note id="GUID-3A08EA4C-9FEB-47DA-9D4E-6A2D68768A50" class="- topic/note "><p class="- topic/p ">Lift the pallet with a lift-truck: 
</p><ul class="- topic/ul "><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> When printer is packed in a crate, lift truck is allowed to lift from all 4 sides. 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> When printer is on pallet without crate, lift truck is only allowed on short side. 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> If lifted on long side pallet with printer could deform (bend) too much. 
</p></li></ul></note></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "/></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">3 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> Be cautious with special ways of transport. 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> Loading printer in a special box looks good, but it is not guaranteed that transport forces stay under allowed limit when fork lift is handling this special transport box could be. 
</p><note type="important" id="GUID-B3777AE5-1012-4AE7-9890-59BD86E4609D" class="- topic/note "><p class="- topic/p "> Also cover protection could damage (dent) the covers of the printer. 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> Do not remove covers of the printer, since fragile or sensitive parts could be exposed to external influences. 
</p></note></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "/></row></tbody></tgroup></table></section></taskbody><related-links class="- topic/related-links "><linkpool class="- topic/linkpool " mapkeyref="GUID-8A41CFEA-5928-4042-A2CB-507A5D034160"><link class="- topic/link " mapclass="- map/topicref " format="dita" type="concept" href="generated-topic-GUID-3955AF8F-9BF3-4DD3-AA2A-175FB2AE2E43.xml" role="parent"><?ditaot usertext?><linktext class="- topic/linktext "><?ditaot usertext?>Installation</linktext></link></linkpool></related-links>
